Figure 3: Number of monthly active users of selected apps in Poland by type and between 2018 and2020

selectivv[[1]] %>%
  mutate(month = as.Date(paste('15', month), format='%d %b %Y')) %>%
  gather(apps, vals, -month) %>%
  filter(vals > 0 ) %>%
  mutate(przewoz = apps %in% c("uber_driver", "bolt_driver", 
                               "i_taxi_kierowca_k3", "free_now_for_drivers"),
         przewoz = ifelse(przewoz, "Transportation", "Delivery")) %>%
  mutate(apps = case_when(apps == "bolt_courier" ~"Bolt Courier",
                          apps == "bolt_driver" ~ "Bolt Driver",
                          apps == "free_now_for_drivers" ~ "Free Now",
                          apps == "glover" ~ "Glover",
                          apps == "i_taxi_kierowca_k3" ~ "iTaxi",
                          apps == "takeaway_com_courier" ~ "Takeaway",
                          apps == "uber_driver" ~ "Uber",
                          apps == "wolt_courier_partner" ~ "Wolt"),
         label = if_else(month == max(month), as.character(apps), NA_character_)) %>%
  ggplot(data = ., aes(x = month, y = vals/1000, color = apps, group = apps)) +
  geom_line(show.legend = FALSE) + 
  geom_text_repel(aes(label = label),
                  nudge_x = -0.25, 
                  direction = "y", 
                  hjust = "left",
                  box.padding = .1,
                  force = .8,
                  na.rm = TRUE,
                  show.legend = FALSE) + 
  scale_color_brewer(type = "qual", palette = "Dark2") + 
  labs(x = "Period", y = 'Number of users (thousands)', color = "App") + 
  facet_wrap(~przewoz, scales = "free_y") +
  scale_x_date(limits = c(as.Date("2018-01-01"), as.Date("2021-09-01"))) + 
  theme(strip.text = element_text(size = 15)) ->  p1

cities_bael %>%
  filter(region_name != "M. Sopot", period == "2020.1") %>%
  filter(!is.na(y))  %>%
  mutate(share = users_cities/y*100,
         share_hi = users_cities / (y - 1.96*rmse)*100,
         share_lo = users_cities / (y + 1.96*rmse)*100,
         region_name = str_remove(region_name, "M. ")) %>%
  mutate(apps = case_when(apps == "bolt_courier" ~"Bolt Courier",
                          apps == "bolt_driver" ~ "Bolt Driver",
                          apps == "free_now_for_drivers" ~ "FREE NOW",
                          apps == "glover" ~ "Glover",
                          apps == "i_taxi_kierowca_k3" ~ "iTaxi",
                          apps == "takeaway_com_courier" ~ "Takeaway",
                          apps == "uber_driver" ~ "Uber",
                          apps == "wolt_courier_partner" ~ "Wolt"),
         apps = factor(apps, c("Uber", "Bolt Driver", "iTaxi", "FREE NOW",
                               "Takeaway", "Wolt", "Glover",  "Bolt Courier"))) %>%
  ggplot(data = ., aes(x = reorder(region_name, -y), y = share, ymin = share_lo, ymax = share_hi)) +

Figure 6 Average and standard deviation (Std. Dev.) of activity time by app type, app, weekdays and hours

selectivv[[4]] %>%
  mutate(period = case_when(period == "January - June 2018" ~ "2018.1",
                            period == "July - December 2018" ~ "2018.2",
                            period == "January - June 2019" ~ "2019.1",
                            period == "July - December 2019" ~ "2019.2",
                            period == "January - June 2020" ~ "2020.1", 
                            period == "July - December 2020" ~ "2020.2")) %>%
  gather(times, vals, -period, -app) %>%
  separate(times, c("day", "day2", "hour"), extra = "merge") %>%
  unite("day", c("day", "day2"), sep = "-") %>%
  mutate(stat = ifelse(str_ends(hour, "std"), "Std.Dev.", "Average"),
         vals = vals / 3600,
         hour = str_remove(hour, "\\_std|\\_s"),
         hour = ifelse(str_detect(hour, "18_00_8_00"), "night (18-8)", "day (8-18)"),
         day  = factor(day, c("monday-thursday", "friday-sunday"), c("Mondays-Thursdays", "Fridays-Sundays")),
         app = case_when(app == "Bolt Courier" ~ "Bolt Courier",
                          app == "Bolt Driver" ~ "Bolt Driver",
                          app == "FREE NOW for drivers" ~ "FREE NOW",
                          app == "Glover" ~ "Glover",
                          app == "iTaxi Kierowca K3" ~ "iTaxi",
                          app == "Takeaway.com Courier" ~ "Takeaway",
                          app == "Uber Driver" ~ "Uber",
                          app == "Wolt Courier Partner" ~ "Wolt"),
         app = factor(app, c("Uber", "Bolt Driver", "iTaxi", "FREE NOW",
                             "Bolt Courier", "Takeaway", "Wolt", "Glover")),
         przewoz = app %in% c("Uber", "Bolt Driver", "iTaxi", "FREE NOW"),
         przewoz = ifelse(przewoz, "Transport", "Delivery"))  %>%
  ggplot(data = ., aes(x = period, y = vals, color = app, group = app)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() + 
  facet_nested(day ~ przewoz +  hour + stat)  +
  scale_color_brewer(type = "qual", palette = "Dark2", name = "Apps") +  
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(x = "Half-year", y = "Average time (in hours)") + 
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0,7,1))  -> p4

Table 7 Direct estimates, its standard errors (in thousands) and sample sizes of the working population size (1864) based on the Labour Force Survey between 2018HY1 and 2020HY

bael %>%
  filter(period == "2018.1")  %>% 
  mutate(region_name = str_remove(region_name, "M. "),
         y = y / 1000,
         rmse = rmse / 1000,
         cv = rmse/y*100) %>%
  select(region_name, size = y, std = rmse, sample = n) %>%
  left_join(
    bael %>%
    filter(period == "2018.2")  %>% 
    mutate(region_name = str_remove(region_name, "M. "),
         y = y / 1000,
         rmse = rmse / 1000,
         cv = rmse/y*100) %>%
    select(region_name, size = y, std = rmse, sample = n),
    by = "region_name"
  ) %>%
  left_join(
    bael %>%
    filter(period == "2019.1")  %>% 
    mutate(region_name = str_remove(region_name, "M. "),
         y = y / 1000,
         rmse = rmse / 1000,
         cv = rmse/y*100) %>%
    select(region_name, size = y, std = rmse, sample = n),
    by = "region_name"
  )  %>%
  left_join(
    bael %>%
